  "prompt": "What do Flipkart's delivery guys look for when I exchange my old phone for a new one?",
  "response": "When a Flipkart delivery person comes to exchange your old phone for a new one, they typically check the following:\n\n**1. Physical Condition:**\n\n*   **Screen Condition:**\n    *   **Cracks/Scratches:** They'll look for cracks, deep scratches, or any damage to the screen. Minor superficial scratches might be acceptable, but major damage will likely result in a rejection of the exchange.\n    *   **Dead Pixels/Lines:** They'll check for any dead pixels, lines, or discoloration on the screen.\n    *   **Touch Functionality:** They might test the touch sensitivity across the entire screen to ensure it's working properly.\n\n*   **Body Condition:**\n    *   **Dents/Damage:** They'll inspect the phone's body for dents, cracks, or significant damage to the frame, back cover, or edges.\n    *   **Broken Buttons:** They'll check if the power button, volume buttons, or home button (if applicable) are functional.\n    *   **Port Condition:** They'll examine the charging port, headphone jack (if present), and SIM card slot for damage or debris.\n\n*   **Camera Condition:**\n    *   **Cracked Lens:** They'll check if the camera lens is cracked or scratched.\n    *   **Functionality:** They might take a quick photo to ensure the camera is working correctly.\n\n**2. Functionality:**\n\n*   **Power On/Off:** They'll make sure the phone can power on and off properly.\n*   **Network Connectivity:** They might check if the phone can connect to a network (Wi-Fi or cellular).\n*   **Calling Functionality:** They may attempt a test call.\n*   **Battery Health:** While they might not have a detailed battery health test, they will be checking if the phone holds a charge. If the phone is dead, or will not charge, that may be an issue.\n\n**3. Originality and Security:**\n\n*   **IMEI Verification:** This is the most important part. They will verify that the IMEI number of the phone matches the one you provided during the exchange process. **This is a crucial step to prevent fraudulent exchanges.**\n*   **No Missing Parts:** Ensure all original components like battery cover or sim tray are present.\n*   **No Third-Party Repairs:** Any evidence of third-party repairs or modifications may result in rejection.\n\n**4. Completeness:**\n\n*   **Phone Only:** Usually, you only need to provide the phone itself.\n*   **Important Note:** Flipkart's exchange policy clearly states what is and is not acceptable. It is HIGHLY recommended to review the terms and conditions related to phone exchanges that are listed on the Flipkart website or app. Failure to meet the requirements outlined there will result in a failed exchange.\n\n**Tips to Ensure a Smooth Exchange:**\n\n*   **Clean the phone:** Wipe the phone clean before the delivery person arrives.\n*   **Back up and erase your data:** Before the delivery person arrives, back up all your important data and perform a factory reset on your phone. This protects your privacy.\n*   **Be honest about the phone's condition:** Accurately describe the phone's condition when initiating the exchange.\n*   **Have the IMEI number ready:** Make sure you know the IMEI number of your phone. You can usually find it in the phone's settings or by dialing \\*#06# on the phone.\n*   **Be present during the inspection:** Be present when the delivery person inspects the phone to answer any questions they may have.\n*   **Review the Exchange Policy:** Before initiating the exchange, carefully read Flipkart's exchange policy to understand the terms and conditions.\n\n**Why are these checks important?**\n\nThese checks are in place to ensure that Flipkart receives a working phone that can be refurbished or recycled. It also prevents fraudulent exchanges and protects both Flipkart and other customers.\n\nBy understanding what the delivery person is looking for, you can prepare your phone for the exchange and increase the chances of a successful transaction.\n",
